=======================================================
  CURRENT SELECTION CRITERIA IN fig_long_record_timeseries()
=======================================================

Function signature:
  fig_long_record_timeseries(
    data_yy, metadata,
    flux_vars = c('NEE_VUT_REF', 'GPP_NT_VUT_REF', 'RECO_NT_VUT_REF',
                  'LE_F_MDS', 'H_F_MDS'),
    n_sites   = 5L,
    geo_level = 'continent'
  )

Continent assignment (R/figures/fig_timeseries.R lines 229-241):
  iso2 <- substr(metadata$site_id, 1L, 2L)
  continent <- .iso2_to_continent(iso2)
  .iso2_to_continent() normalises 'UK' -> 'GB', then calls:
    countrycode::countrycode(iso2_norm, origin='iso2c',
                             destination='continent', warn=FALSE)
  Uses UN Geoscheme 6-continent system.
  Sites with NA continent are dropped before selection.

Record length calculation (line 239):
  span = last_year - first_year   [integer subtraction from snapshot metadata]
  NOTE: span is the calendar span, NOT n_years_valid_nee.
  No actual NEE data coverage check is performed during site selection.

Site selection (lines 244-248):
  selected_sites <- site_meta |>
    group_by(continent) |>
    slice_max(order_by = span, n = n_sites, with_ties = FALSE) |>
    ungroup()
  Selects top n_sites = 5 per continent by maximum span.
  Ties broken arbitrarily (with_ties = FALSE, row order determines winner).

